<subSubSection id="DACA652BD458B527FF7AB02066D08B12" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" type="key">
<key id="E6416191D458B527FF7AB02066D08B12" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<keyStep id="29242E05D458B524FF7AB02066D08FA9" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph id="926F36A0D458B524FF7AB02066D08FC1" blockId="1.[151,1437,1372,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead id="29219595D458B524FF7AB02066D08FC1" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
1. Prepectal carina present in front of precoxal sulcus; occipital carina complete dorsally and area in front of it rugulose; frons with crenulate median groove; precoxal sulcus very wide............................ 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D458B524FBD1B00566D08FC1" authority="Belokobylskij, 1999" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1999" box="[1084,1436,1401,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Orientocolastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D458B524FBD1B00567988FC1" box="[1084,1236,1401,1422]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Orientocolastes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F6414B51D458B524FB37B00566D08FC1" author="Belokobylskij, S. A." box="[1242,1436,1401,1423]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" pagination="155 - 169" refId="ref5940" refString="Belokobylskij, S. A. (1999) New genera of the subfamilies Rhyssalinae, Exothecinae and Gnamptodontinae from the Old World (Hymenoptera: Braconidae). Zoosystematica Rossica, 8 (1), 155 - 169." type="journal article" year="1999">Belokobylskij, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="926F36A0D458B524FF7AB0EB66D08FA9" blockId="1.[151,1437,1372,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead id="29219595D458B524FF7AB0EB66D08FA9" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
- Prepectal carina completely absent (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D458B524FDD3B0EA61C48FE3" box="[574,648,1430,1452]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[194,1393,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2(A–F). Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, lateral view; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) apex of antenna; (D) base of antenna; (E) head, frontal view; (F) mesosoma, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D, E, F); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521271/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
); occipital carina usually absent dorsally, 
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D458B524FBF6B0EA67668FE3" bold="true" box="[1051,1066,1430,1452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">if</emphasis>
present then area in front of it smooth (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D458B524FF04B0C862758F86" box="[233,313,1460,1482]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3(A–G). (A–E) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, dorsal view; (B) mesosoma, dorsal view; (C) metasoma, dorsal view; (D) apex of metasoma, showing ovipositor sheath and ovipositor; (E) ovipositor; (F–G) paratype, female. (F) Pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (G) propodeum + metasomal tergite I, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, B, C, D, F, G); 0.1 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521273/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D458B524FEAEB0C8622F8F85" box="[323,355,1460,1482]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[199,1387,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[199,1388,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4(A–D). (A) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, female, metasoma, dorsal view; (B–D), paratype, male; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) head + pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (D) mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521275/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">4C</figureCitation>
); frons without crenulate median groove; precoxal sulcus absent or narrow (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D458B524FBACB0C867C78F85" box="[1089,1163,1460,1482]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[194,1393,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2(A–F). Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, lateral view; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) apex of antenna; (D) base of antenna; (E) head, frontal view; (F) mesosoma, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D, E, F); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521271/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
); but distinctly developed in 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D458B524FF0FB0AD62798FA9" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1833" box="[226,309,1489,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Colastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D458B524FF0FB0AD62798FA9" box="[226,309,1489,1510]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Colastes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D458B524FEAEB0AD61378FA8" authority="Belokobylskij, 2000" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="2000" box="[323,635,1489,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Discolastes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D458B524FEAEB0AD62FE8FA9" box="[323,434,1489,1510]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Discolastes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F6414B51D458B524FE5AB0AD61378FA8" author="Belokobylskij, S. A." box="[439,635,1489,1511]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" pagination="180 - 203" refId="ref5981" refString="Belokobylskij, S. A. (2000) New taxa of the subfamily Exothecinae (Hymenoptera, Braconidae) from tropical and subtropical regions of the Old World. II. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 79 (1), 180 - 203. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="2000">Belokobylskij, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
)................................................................ 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="29242E05D458B524FF7AB09266D08C6E" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph id="926F36A0D458B524FF7AB09266D08C4C" blockId="1.[151,1437,1372,2039]" box="[151,1436,1518,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead id="29219595D458B524FF7AB09266D08C4C" box="[151,1436,1518,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">2. Pronope absent or small, shallow and transverse, rarely medium-sized; clypeus convex............................. 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="926F36A0D458B524FF7AB37066D08C6E" blockId="1.[151,1437,1372,2039]" box="[151,1436,1548,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead id="29219595D458B524FF7AB37066D08C6E" box="[151,1436,1548,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
- Pronope present, large and deep (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D458B524FDCFB37061268C6D" box="[546,618,1548,1570]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3(A–G). (A–E) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, dorsal view; (B) mesosoma, dorsal view; (C) metasoma, dorsal view; (D) apex of metasoma, showing ovipositor sheath and ovipositor; (E) ovipositor; (F–G) paratype, female. (F) Pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (G) propodeum + metasomal tergite I, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, B, C, D, F, G); 0.1 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521273/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
); sometimes obsolescent in 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D458B524FC95B37060988C6E" authorityName="Foerster" authorityYear="1863" box="[888,980,1548,1569]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Xenarcha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D458B524FC95B37060988C6E" box="[888,980,1548,1569]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Xenarcha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; clypeus flattened..................... 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="29242E05D458B524FF7AB35566D08CFC" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph id="926F36A0D458B524FF7AB35566D08C36" blockId="1.[151,1437,1372,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead id="29219595D458B524FF7AB35566D08C36" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
3. Metasomal tergite V markedly enlarged, bent posteriorly and concealing subsequent tergites; tergites I–V entirely sculptured; male without occipital carina, but large temporal tubercles developed; malar suture distinct.................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D458B524FB8CB31866D08C36" authority="Belokobylskij, 1994" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1994" box="[1121,1436,1636,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Vietcolastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D458B524FB8CB318679F8C36" box="[1121,1235,1636,1657]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Vietcolastes</emphasis>
Belokobylskij, 1994
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="926F36A0D458B524FF7AB3FD66D08CFC" blockId="1.[151,1437,1372,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead id="29219595D458B524FF7AB3FD66D08CFC" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
- Metasomal tergite V normal; tergites II–V either smooth or sculptured; in both sexes occipital carina developed and temporal tubercles absent; malar suture indistinct or obsolescent..................................... 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D458B524FB50B3E266D08CFC" authority="Haliday, 1833" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1833" box="[1213,1436,1694,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Colastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D458B524FB50B3E2665C8CFC" box="[1213,1296,1694,1715]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Colastes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F6414B51D458B524FAFBB3E266D08CFC" author="Haliday, A. H." box="[1302,1436,1694,1716]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" pagination="333 - 350" refId="ref6542" refString="Haliday, A. H. (1833) An essay on the classification of the parasitic Hymenoptera of Britain, which correspond with the Ichneumones minuti of Linnaeus. Entomological Magazine, 1 (iii), 259 - 276, 333 - 350." type="journal article" year="1833">Haliday, 1833</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="29242E05D458B524FF7AB3C066D08D08" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph id="926F36A0D458B524FF7AB3C066D08D44" blockId="1.[151,1437,1372,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead id="29219595D458B524FF7AB3C066D08D44" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
4. Tergites I–III forming a carapace-like metasoma, coarsely longitudinally striate, and their epipleura less sclerotised than their nota; remaining tergites covered by tergites I-III or largely so; tergite III on posterior margin with more or less distinct transparent border........................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D458B524FB80B38A66D08D44" authority="Belokobylskij, 1984" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1984" box="[1133,1436,1782,1804]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Colastinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D458B524FB80B38A67988D44" box="[1133,1236,1782,1803]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Colastinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F6414B51D458B524FB37B38A66D08D44" author="Belokobylskij, S. A." box="[1242,1436,1782,1804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" pagination="1019 - 1026" refId="ref5674" refString="Belokobylskij, S. A. (1984) On the division of the tribe Exothecini s. l. (Hymenoptera, Braconidae) in two with the description of a new genus and subgenus. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 63, 1019 - 1026. [in Russian with English summary]" type="journal article" year="1984">Belokobylskij, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="926F36A0D458B524FF7AB26866D08D08" blockId="1.[151,1437,1372,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead id="29219595D458B524FF7AB26866D08D08" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">- Tergites I–III not forming a carapace-like metasoma, with their epipleura and nota equally sclerotised; remaining tergites distinctly exposed, tergite III along posterior margin without transparent border................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="29242E05D458B524FF7AB23266D08DF3" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph id="926F36A0D458B524FF7AB23266D08DD1" blockId="1.[151,1437,1372,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead id="29219595D458B524FF7AB23266D08DD1" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
5. Occipital carina complete, ventrally reaching up to base of mandible (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D458B524FC7FB23260A88D2C" box="[914,996,1870,1892]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[181,1406,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3(A–G). (A–E) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., holotype, female. (A) Head, dorsal view; (B) mesosoma, dorsal view; (C) metasoma, dorsal view; (D) apex of metasoma, showing ovipositor sheath and ovipositor; (E) ovipositor; (F–G) paratype, female. (F) Pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (G) propodeum + metasomal tergite I, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, B, C, D, F, G); 0.1 mm (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521273/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D458B524FC02B23267418D2C" box="[1007,1037,1870,1891]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[199,1387,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[199,1388,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4(A–D). (A) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, female, metasoma, dorsal view; (B–D), paratype, male; (B) habitus, lateral view; (C) head + pronotum, dorsal view, showing pronope; (D) mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A, C, D); 0.5 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521275/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">4C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D458B524FBF4B23267198D2B" box="[1049,1109,1870,1892]" captionStart="FIGURES 6" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,184,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[160,1428,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 6(A–E). Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., head, latero-posterior view. (A) Holotype, female; (B–E) paratypes. (B–D) females; (E) male. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521283/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">6A–E</figureCitation>
); first subdiscal cell of fore wing elongate (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D458B524FEADB21062F58DCE" box="[320,441,1899,1922]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1983,2007]" captionTargetBox="[202,1385,597,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-216@7.[202,1385,597,1959]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5(A–D). (A, D) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, male. (A) Metasoma, dorsal view; (D) fore wing; (B–C) paratype, female. (B) fore wing; (C) hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521281" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521281/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Figs 5B, 5D</figureCitation>
); fore wing vein 1-M of male widened, as wide as or wider than the length of vein cu-a (
<figureCitation id="0AEB2A25D458B524FAE6B210661B8DCE" box="[1291,1367,1899,1922]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1983,2007]" captionTargetBox="[202,1385,597,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-216@7.[202,1385,597,1959]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5(A–D). (A, D) Occipitotus langpramensis sp. nov., paratype, male. (A) Metasoma, dorsal view; (D) fore wing; (B–C) paratype, female. (B) fore wing; (C) hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521281" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521281/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
)...................................................................................... 
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D458B524FB21B2F566D08DD1" bold="true" box="[1228,1436,1929,1950]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D458B524FB21B2F566708DD1" authority="Singh &amp; Achterberg &amp; Sheela, 2022" authorityName="Singh &amp; Achterberg &amp; Sheela" authorityYear="2022" box="[1228,1340,1929,1950]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Occipitotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D458B524FB21B2F566708DD1" bold="true" box="[1228,1340,1929,1950]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Occipitotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BB9757C9D458B524FAAFB2F566D08DD1" box="[1346,1436,1929,1950]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="926F36A0D458B524FF7AB2DB66D08DF3" blockId="1.[151,1437,1372,2039]" box="[151,1436,1958,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead id="29219595D458B524FF7AB2DB66D08DF3" box="[151,1436,1958,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">- Occipital carina incomplete, dorsally interrupted; first subdiscal cell of fore wing broad; fore wing vein slender.......... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="29242E05D458B527FF7AB2B866D08A85" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph id="926F36A0D458B524FF7AB2B866D08DB9" blockId="1.[151,1437,1372,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead id="29219595D458B524FF7AB2B866D08DB9" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">
6. Metasomal tergites I–V entirely sculptured; apical tergites not protruding (or only slightly) beyond tergite V; tergites IV and V with a lateral crease.................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D458B524FBF1B29D66D08DB9" authority="Belokobylskij, 1984" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1984" box="[1052,1436,2017,2039]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Pseudophanomeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D458B524FBF1B29D67988DB9" box="[1052,1236,2017,2038]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="41">Pseudophanomeris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F6414B51D458B524FB37B29D66D08DB9" author="Belokobylskij, S. A." box="[1242,1436,2017,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" pagination="1019 - 1026" refId="ref5674" refString="Belokobylskij, S. A. (1984) On the division of the tribe Exothecini s. l. (Hymenoptera, Braconidae) in two with the description of a new genus and subgenus. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 63, 1019 - 1026. [in Russian with English summary]" type="journal article" year="1984">Belokobylskij, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="926F36A0D45BB527FF7AB5E466D08A85" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,349]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
<keyLead id="29219595D45BB527FF7AB5E466D08A85" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">- Metasomal tergites less sculptured, at most tergite III completely and base of tergite IV sculptured; apical tergites distinctly protruding beyond tergite V; tergites IV and V without a lateral crease........................................... 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="29242E05D45BB527FF7AB5AF66D08B12" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
<paragraph id="926F36A0D45BB527FF7AB5AF66D08B6D" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,349]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
<keyLead id="29219595D45BB527FF7AB5AF66D08B6D" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
7. Posterior half of notauli absent or obsolescent; vein r of fore wing usually departing between basal third and base of pterostigma; if departing near basal 0.4 of pterostigma, then vein m-cu of fore wing distinctly converging to vein 1-M posteriorly................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D45BB527FB84B47166D08B6D" authority="van Achterberg, 1983" authorityName="van Achterberg" authorityYear="1983" box="[1129,1436,269,291]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Shawiana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D45BB527FB84B47167848B6D" box="[1129,1224,269,290]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">Shawiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F6414B51D45BB527FB20B47166D08B6D" author="van Achterberg, C." box="[1229,1436,269,291]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" pagination="339 - 355" refId="ref7063" refString="van Achterberg, C. (1983) Revisionary notes on the Palaearctic genera and species of the tribe Exothecini Foerster (Hymenoptera, Braconidae). Zoologische Mededelingen, Leiden, 57, 339 - 355." type="journal article" year="1983">van Achterberg, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="926F36A0D45BB527FF7AB45766D08B12" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,349]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
<keyLead id="29219595D45BB527FF7AB45766D08B12" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
- Posterior half of notauli distinctly impressed, (nearly) complete; vein r of fore wing departing from basal 0.4–0.6 of pterostigma and vein m-cu of fore wing less converging posteriorly.................................... 
<taxonomicName id="55D04D23D45BB527FB5DB43B66D08B12" authority="Foerster, 1863" authorityName="Foerster" authorityYear="1863" box="[1200,1436,327,349]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Xenarcha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0A4EAB2D45BB527FB5DB43B66408B13" box="[1200,1292,327,348]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">Xenarcha</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F6414B51D45BB527FAFEB43466D08B12" author="Foerster, A." box="[1299,1436,327,349]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" pagination="225 - 288" refId="ref6508" refString="Foerster, A. (1863) Synopsis der Familien und Gattungen der Braconen. Verhandlungen des Naturhistorischen Vereines der Preussischen Rheinlande und Westphalens, 19, 225 - 288. [1862]" type="journal article" year="1863">Foerster, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
